## Tarball fallback
```
build: git -C ~/Pitcher-Injury-Risk archive --format=tar.gz -o <path> <base-sha>
```

## Restore contract (proposed — see CONTRACT-NOTE.md)
Needs a Python venv with pandas + numpy (from PIR requirements.txt). The check uses
tiny synthetic input, so committed Statcast parquet data is NOT required.
  1. Materialize base into a temp dir.
  2. python -m venv + pip install pandas numpy  (or a cached venv).
  3. Run `claude -p` with that dir as cwd.
  4. Pass dir to check.sh as WORKSPACE_DIR; check runs the property-based test against
     src/features/workload_features.py.
